[2] USA: measles cases continue to increase
Date: Mon 3 Jun 2019
Source: NBC [abridged, edited]
http://kobi5.com/news/measles-cases-continue-to-increase-103310/


Confirmed cases of the measles continue to creep up. The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) is reporting that there are now 981 cases in 26 states as of last Friday [31 May 2019]. That is an increase of 41 cases from the previous week.

Over 800 of the cases are in New York, and the majority of those were in people who not vaccinated. This is the most cases reported in the country since 1992. The agency warned last week that the USA may lose its measles elimination status if the outbreak continues through the summer and the fall.

The disease was declared eliminated back in 2000.

The states that have reported cases to CDC are Arizona, California, Colorado, Connecticut, Florida, Georgia, Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kentucky, Maine, Maryland, Massachusetts, Michigan, Missouri, New Mexico, Nevada, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Oklahoma, Oregon, Pennsylvania, Texas, Tennessee, and Washington.

