[It's bad enough the antivaxxers are putting children directly and indirectly in harm's way by creating pockets of susceptibles that permit circulation of the measles virus in a community and in addition to endangering those unvaccinated children, they are endangering those children who could not be vaccinated for medical reasons. Now they are selling snake oil treatments for autism and "immune boosting" to protect against diseases such as measles. As my colleague Mod.LK says, a history lesson is in order -- how many children were hospitalized and how many died due to measles before there was an effective vaccine. Millions of dollars have been spent looking at the theory of autism and its relationship to vaccinations, and no association has been found through the years since the fateful false study of Wakefield was published in Lancet. - Mod.MPP]

