[5] USA: New York (Sullivan County)
Date: Wed 5 Jun 2019
Source: Times Herald-Record [abridged, edited]
https://www.recordonline.com/news/20190605/sullivan-reports-3-new-measles-cases-total-now-5
and http://healthmap.org/ln.php?6505863&u8901


The Sullivan County Public Health Department reported 3 new cases of measles Tue [4 Jun 2019] and warns of 3 places in Kiamesha Lake and Fallsburg where others may have been exposed to it.

Since March [2019], Sullivan County now has 5 confirmed measles cases, as well as 2 suspect cases.

Two people confirmed to be contagious are under quarantine per a mandatory isolation order issued by Sullivan County Public Health Director Nancy McGraw, according to a news release from the county.

[See URL for locations and times of possible exposure.]

Sullivan County has been preparing for measles for a few months in anticipation of the annual summer migration of downstate residents and visitors that triples its population, as well as a massive outbreak of the disease in New York City and Rockland County. As of this week, there are 566 confirmed cases in the city and 255 in Rockland County, largely among unvaccinated children in the orthodox Jewish community.

Last week, the county legislature adopted a public health order that mandates summer camps require their campers and staff to be vaccinated against the measles.

