[6] USA: New York (Rockland County): mandatory vaccination for campers
Date: Thu 6 Jun 2019
Source: Clarkstown Daily Voice [abridged, edited]
https://dailyvoice.com/new-york/clarkstown/news/as-measles-cases-climb-rockland-summer-campers-required-to-be-vaccinated/769631/


As the number of measles cases climbs again in Rockland County to 256 confirmed cases, health department officials are offering additional free vaccine clinics and notifying parents that all children attending summer camp will be required to be vaccinated.

According to Health Commissioner Dr. Patricia Schnabel Ruppert, all children attending summer camp and all camp staff must have been vaccinated for the measles in order to work or attend any Rockland County camp. The orders include day camps, traveling summer day camps, and children's overnight camps.

"For all the families who have already had their children vaccinated, this should be as simple as getting a document from your doctor," said County Executive Ed Day.

To help make it a fun summer for all and keep everyone safe, the department is offering a host of free MMR vaccine clinics.

[Byline: Kathy Reakes]

