[14] Ukraine
Date: Tue 4 Jun 2019
Source: International Society [abridged, edited]
https://112.international/society/three-month-old-child-dies-from-measles-in-rivne-40379.html


Another death from measles was registered in Rivne city, western Ukraine. A 3-month-old child died from the complications caused by this disease, Rivne Regional Lab Center reported.

It is reported that a girl was born by a woman who was infected with measles during the pregnancy. A child was born premature and had congenital measles. The virus struck the brain and lungs of the child. All necessary resuscitation events took place; however, it was impossible to save a child.

The diagnosis of measles was confirmed at the virological labs.

It is noted that 74 citizens of Rivne region, including 60 children, were infected with measles last week. A total of 25 ill people, including 14 children, were hospitalized.

As we reported 50 749 people, including 24 905 adults and 26 844 children, have been sickened with measles in Ukraine in 2019. Earlier, the UN reported that 70% of all measles cases in Europe are observed in Ukraine.

Besides, all adults will get the vaccines against measles for free. Acting Healthcare Minister Ulyana Suprun reported that another 780 000 vaccines against measles will be bought by Ukraine in 2019.

