[16] Australia (New South Wales, Sydney): alert
Date: Thu 6 Jun 2019
Source: The Sydney Morning Herald [abridged, edited]
https://www.smh.com.au/national/nsw/sydney-measles-alert-cathay-pacific-flight-airport-and-south-west-20190606-p51v3j.html


Passengers on an international flight to Sydney Airport [NSW, Australia] and a train to Sydney's south-west have been warned to look out for measles symptoms. A man in his 40s travelled on a Cathay Pacific flight to Sydney from Bangladesh

[See source URL for details on flight and train.]

It can take up to 18 days for symptoms to appear following exposure to a person with measles.

This alert brings the total number of measles cases in NSW to 36, including 8 children under the age of 5.

NSW Health director of communicable diseases, Dr. Vicky Sheppeard, said none of the locations visited by the man pose an ongoing risk.

It is not known if the man was fully vaccinated against measles.

More than 95% of 5-year-olds in NSW are vaccinated against measles.

[Byline: Kate Aubusson]

